Short History
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The commonly accepted source of origin of common algebra is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

The Compendious Book on Calculation by Completion and Balancing
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, with its original arabic name 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

الْكِتَابْ الْمُخْتَصَرْ فِيْ حِسَابْ الْجَبْرْ وَالْمُقَابَلَة
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, that is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Al-kitāb al-mukhtaṣar fī ḥisāb al-ğabr wa’l-muqābala
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Written by persian mathematician Polymath Muḥammad ibn Mūsā al-Khwārizmī
 in 820CE.
 
\end_layout

